Title : Johann Jakob Guggenbühl
Text : '''Johann Jakob Guggenbühl''' (August 13, 1816, [[Meilen]] – February 2, 1863 [[Montreux]]) was a Swiss physician.<ref>http://www.hls-dhs-dss.ch/textes/d/D14393.php Guggenbühl, Johann Jakob - Historisches Lexikon der Schweiz.</ref> He's considered as one of the precursors of medico-educational care.

[[Image:Guggenbühl.jpg|thumb|Johann Jakob Guggenbühl with children of his hospital, 1853.]]

== Life ==
Guggenbühl showed interest in [[cretinism]] and was convinced that this disease could be cured. He created, in 1841, a residential home for mentally-handicapped children in [[Interlaken]] that lasted until 1860.

== Works ==
* ''Hülfsruf aus den Alpen, zur Bekämpfung des schrecklichen Cretinismus.'' In: ''Maltens Bibliothek der neuesten Weltkunde.'' Band 1, Aarau 1840, p.&nbsp;191 et seq.
* ''Briefe über den Abendberg und die Heilanstalt für Cretinismus'', 1846.
* ''Die Heilung und Verhütung des Cretinismus und ihre neuesten Fortschritte'', 1853.

